<h3>Rules of reviewing of articles</h3>
<ol>
	<li>Peer review (expert assessment), manuscripts of scientific papers, scientific reviews, peer review and feedback (hereinafter - scientific articles) in the magazine &quot;Black Holes in the Russian legislation&quot; is carried out to maintain the high scientific and theoretical level of the publication and for the selection of the most valuable and relevant ( looking) papers.</li>
	<li>In the journal &quot;The black hole in the Russian legislation&quot; bilateral blind (anonymous) review is established :</li>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li>personal data of the author/authors is not disclosed to the referee;</li>
	<li>author/authors do not receive the personal data of reviewer.</li>
</ul>
<ol>
	<li>The articles received are passing the primary control on the completeness and correctness of registration in accordance with Regulation destinations articles.</li>
	<li>The initial expert evaluation of scientific articles is performed by the chief editor or deputy editor.</li>
	<li>Editor in chief (deputy editor) determines under reviewer member of the editorial board, supervising the appropriate direction (scientific discipline).</li>
	<li>In the absence of a member of the editorial board, supervising the appropriate direction (scientific discipline), editor in chief (deputy editor) defines an external reviewer.</li>
</ol>
<p>Reviewers (members of the Editorial Board and external) should be recognized experts on the subject of the peer-reviewed articles and have the publications on the theme of a peer-reviewed article for the past three years,.</p>
<ol start="6">
	<li>Required are reviewed scientific articles, the scientific articles from authors who have no degree or have a degree of candidate of Sciences are referred in mandatory order.</li>
</ol>
<p>Scientific articles received from authors who have a PhD, including the members of the editorial board, are reviewed at the direction of editor in chief (deputy editor).</p>
<ol start="7">
	<li>After the peer review of the scientific article reviewer can:</li>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li>recommend an article for publication;</li>
	<li>recommend an article for publication after revised in light of comments;</li>
	<li>not to recommend the article for publication.</li>
</ul>
<p>If the reviewer recommends an article to be published after revision, based on the comments, or does not recommend an article to be published, the review should contain the reasons for the decision.</p>
<p>The editorial board recommend to use a standard form of reviews.</p>
<ol start="8">
	<li>When reviewing scientific articles Reviewers are required to:</li>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li>pay attention to the relevance of the scientific problems ;</li>
	<li>describe the importance of theoretical and applied research;</li>
	<li>evaluate how the author&#39;s conclusions relate to the existing scientific concepts.</li>
</ul>
<p>The assessment of the author&#39;s personal contribution &nbsp;in the solution of the problem should be an essential element of the review.</p>
<p>It is worth noting in a review of compliance with the style of presentation logic and the availability of the scientific nature of the material, as well as to the conclusion of the reliability and validity of conclusions.</p>
<p>It is worth noting <span data-align="2710:2720">in a r</span>eview of the correspondence of style, logic and accessibility of presentation, scientific character of the material, as well as to make a conclusion about the reliability and validity of the conclusions.</p>
<ol start="9">
	<li>The presence of a substantial proportion of the criticisms the reviewer with an overall positive recommendation can be attributed to the category of polemical material and print it in the manner of scientific discussion.</li>
	<li>Scientific articles may be sent for further review. The grounds for re-review are:</li>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li>insufficient qualification in matters dealt with in a scientific article, stated by expert (s);</li>
	<li>insufficient level of initial expert opinion;</li>
	<li>the disputable provisions made in the scientific article.</li>
</ul>
<ol start="11">
	<li>The reviewer sends the review &nbsp;to the editor in the form of scanned copies by e-mail or in hard copy by mail.</li>
	<li>&nbsp;The editorial board sends copies of reviews or the reasoned refusal to the authors of submissions (in anonimous form, according to the p.2 of this Regulation).</li>
	<li>The editorial board transmit copies of reviews to the Ministry of Education and Science of the Russian Federation when requested.</li>
	<li>&nbsp;Reviews are stored at the editorial office for 5 years.</li>
</ol>


